Product name: Vintage Joseff of Hollywood Earrings
Description:
"Wow" is the first word that comes to mind when looking at these vintage copper Joseff earrings. Especially if you know anything about the designer's reputation in the industry!!!
These earrings have a twisty 2 1/2 inch drop from the clip/lobe. The clips are in tight/good working condition. The earrings are signed and would be a statement piece or a valuable addition for a collector.
Known as the "jeweler to the stars," Joseff of Hollywood Jewelry made it's reputation by providing the vast majority of jewelry used in Hollywood movies during the 1930's, 1940's and 1950's (although he did not make jewelry from 1942-1944). Owner and designer Eugene Joseff created jewelry as glamorous as the era and place in which he worked. "Gone With The Wind" and "Around the World in Eighty Days" are just two of many movies enhanced by Joseff jewelry.
He wanted the jewelry used in period movies to have a basis in historical fact, and the combination of the requirements of the movie industry and his own creative genius resulted in some of the most fabulous jewelry of ever made. 
Mr. Joseff died in 1948, and his wife, Joan Castle Joseff has spearheaded Joseff jewelry since that time. Joan Joseff branched out into providing Joseff jewelry for TV stars from the Fifties on, as well as expanding the retail market until her death in 2010. 
Earring Length- 3 1/2 inches
Thanks for looking!!!!!!!

Knitting needles sizes 5, 8 and 9 or size to give gauge
1 dp or cable needle
6 buttons
Gauge:  6 sts = 1 inch; 6 rows = 1 inch.

Pattern comes with at least two PDF files; one for the pattern and one containing conversion charts for knitting needle sizes, crochet hook sizes (metric,US,UK/Can,JPN), crochet terminology,(US,UK/AU), a yarn weight chart and a standard metric conversion chart. Description:
This is a vintage Liz Claiborne women's eyeglass frame that is new old stock. The frame is goldtone and purple. It is marked LC-67, V10  made in Japan. The eye size is 52 mm,  bridge size 18 mm and temple length is 140 mm. The lens depth is 45 mm. There is very minor scratches on the inside temple area. There are no demo lenses in this frame. 
New old stock frames are frames that have not been worn. These will be sturdier than putting your prescription into a 
frame that formerly held prescription lenses and worn. Wearing a plastic frame ages the plastic as it is heated by the 
wearer, slowly aging the plastic, making it more brittle over time. The same can be said for the nosepads on a metal 
frame, but these are replacable. Please look at the above measurements for this frame. Compare them to the 
sizing of your current frame. There are markings on all optical shop frames. Choosing a frame of similiar measurements
will increase your satisfaction with your new frame purchase. Sometimes a trip to the optical shop to try on frames of 
the same of similiar sizing will be a time saver in the end.
I work in the eye care industry and have for the past 30 years and have a special interest in eyeglass frames. 
I price at a fraction of the price of new, modern frames. I have a large quantity of frames that were stored for 30 years  
after an optical shop closed. These are "new, old stock". Most have demo lenses. These lenses may be scratched or cracked.
I have included them as they were original to the frame. There may be slight imperfections in the frame that are listed
above. I listed with as many photos as allowed. If you have any questions or need more photos please contact me. 
Frames are sold WITHOUT WARRANTY. If an optical shop breaks your frame while it is in their hands, you will have

Product name: PIN-UP CARDS, Complete Deck of "The Petty Girls 2", George Petty, 1995, Vintage Girlie, Glamour Art
Description:
George Petty embraced the world of pin up or, girlie art like no other artist.  His girls were naughty, but dream-like...a Petty Girl can not be mistaken for another's artwork.  He had a long career and created beautiful artwork mainly for Esquire and True Magazines.
His real claim to fame in the pin-up world is how popular his girls were for "nose art" painted on planes in World War II, including the famous Memphis Belle.
This is a deck of cards No. 51 -100 in the second series of "The Petty Girls" issued by 21st Century Archives in 1995.  Each card features a Petty girl on the front and a description or comment on the back with the original year each drawing was created.  The deck covers reproduction of artwork done for Esquire Magazine from 1933 until 1956.
The deck is complete and in great condition...another piece from my husband's extensive pin-up collection...I may never through it!

Product name: Rare Limited First Edition Princess Diana Beanie Baby, REDUCED With no Space Tag, 1997 made in Indonisia, P.E.Pellets in Pristine Condition
Description:
REDUCED FOR ONE WEEK ONLY
A wonderful genuine collectable Princess Diana Beanie Baby.
Made in plush purple with Swing tag (still in plastic protector) and tush tag.
This bear is a rare First Edition which was made in Indonesia.  It contains P.E. Pellets
The identification of a First Edition is based on the Swing Tag having no spaces in between the wording.
Princess swing tags are often referred to by collectors as "space" or "no-space". This is a reference to the last four lines of text on the right inside of the swing tag. A "first edition" Princess MUST have the "no-space" swing tag attached.
All profits of Ty from this collectible 
will be donated to the 
DIANA, PRINCESS OF WALES 
MEMORIAL FUND 
This wonderful bear comes from a private collector.  She is slowly selling her collection and this is the first one for sale. It is in pristine condition with no yellowing to the Swing Tag or crease in the tush tag.  Taken out of protective packaging to photo graph only.
One to add to your collection or even start you off on your journey of being a Beanie Baby Collector.
I can provide more photographs if required

Over the coming months as I grow my Etsy shop I will be adding more themed and colour co-ordinated collections, mint and used sets of stamps from all over the world. If you don't already, why not start collecting vintage stamps? They are beautiful things to collect – colourful, cute and full of character. In my shop I (will!) have loads of stamps to start your collection today all at very competitive prices. I try to check my prices regularly against other dealers and EBay so rest assured you’ll be getting excellent quality stamps at a fair price.
Personally I collect used and mint Great Britain, with a specialist machin collection, mint Bermuda and Australia. Find out what interests you! Description:
NEW SHOP PROMO - USE COUPON WHOLESOMEBATHBOMBS FOR 10% OFF 
Buying bulk order seems more expensive, but you get to save over 15 on shipping!
We offer multiple sizes, medium size being a heavy 6-8oz and larger than a tennis ball and large size (more XL) 10-12oz and much larger than a tennis ball at 3.15oz. IF YOU BUY 2 MINI, PLEASE NOTE THAT THEY ARE FOR SAMPLE ONLY AND WILL NOT FULLY COLOR/FRAGRANCE YOUR TUB.
Spice up any bath with this relaxing and rejuvenating activated charcoal bath bomb. This bath bomb will turn your bath water pitch black! Please note that these bath bombs are packed with a lot of detoxifying activated charcoal. This means that it has the potential to lightly stain you and your tub. Taking a light shower after will get rid of any stains on your body and most of it off the tub. 
Recommended fragrances: 
This bath bomb is great with any fragrance you'd like :) 
Sizes:
Our bath bombs are quite large and more compact than others so you may use one multiple times. Mini size is around 1.40" and 1-2oz. We recommend using all 4 in one bath. Medium size is 2.75" and 6-8oz. We recommend using one for up to 2 baths. Large sizes are 3.15" and 10-12oz. We recommend the large one for up to 3 uses. You can easily cut them into slices with a sharp knife or you can just use one whole bath bomb for one bath. For the fullest coloration and fragrance, we recommend using the whole bath bomb. 
Shipping & Packaging:
All bath bombs are placed in a biodegradable plant-based plastic bag and a kraft twist tie. There are labeled stickers on both sides of the bag and a how to use guide. They will be shipped in a box, size depending on the order quantity and size. The bath bomb is padded with thin packing paper to prevent cracking/breakage. They will be shipped within 3-9 days after the purchase and you can pick the shipping plans you want. For larger orders exceeding 5 bath bombs, please expect a delay as it will take a longer time to create and pack. 
Please check ingredients for possible allergies. If any irritation occurs, please stop using. Avoid getting the bath water directly into your eyes, as you would do with most other bath/shower products.
All our fragrance oils are phthalate free. However, if you are still worried about fragrance oils, you can pick natural essential oils (with the EO ending) instead.
All our ingredients are cruelty-free and we don't conduct nor condone any animal testing in any of our products.
There might be staining, but you should very easily be able to clean it up with water. If not, a sponge and cleaner may also work. There should be no harsh staining, though.
If you have any more questions, feel free to contact us!

Parts  Used: Leave

The health benefits of peppermint oil include its ability to treat indigestion, respiratory problems, headache, nausea, fever, stomach and bowel spasms and pain. Due to the presence of menthol, menthone and menthyl esters, peppermint and peppermint oil find wide applications in manufacture of soap, shampoo, cigarette, toothpaste, chewing gum, tea and ice cream.
Peppermint is a cross between watermint and spearmint and is native to Europe. Historically, the herb has been known for its medicinal uses, and its impressively long history often gives it the prestigious title as the world’s oldest medicine.
Precautions of Peppermint Essential Oil
 Do not apply to skin to be exposed to sunlight or ultraviolet light; it increases the skin’s photo sensitivity.  it may irritate sensitive skin. Always test for skin sensitivity prior to widespread use and use on the feet when possible. Excessive use of any oil can lead to skin sensitization. Keep out of eyes, ears, or nose. Not all oils are created equal, so test it carefully, and it is better to avoid any essential oil throughout Pregnancy.

Product name: 4 Feet, 18ga Copper Solder Wire, Brazing Wire, Made in USA, 93% Copper
Description:
Four feet (48") of wire.  I am providing this wire in two formats (please state your preference in the comments at checkout):
93% pure copper solder / brazing wire.  7% phosphorus
Specs:
Country of Origin:  USA
Melt Temp:  1310 F  710 C
Flow Temp:  1460 F  793 C
Thickness:  18ga (approx 1mm)
Flow:  Fast
Ductility:  Poor.  (not for use on ferrous or nickel based materials because the joint will become brittle and may fail).
Best Uses:  Copper, brass, bronze.   Always flux brass and bronze joints.  No need to use flux on copper but flux will help with preventing some firescale.
A tiny quantity of this is all you need for torch soldering bezels and jump rings!  I use this to solder jump rings and bezels made from the #110 copper wire that I also sell.   Please note that I do not claim for this material to be a "color match."  Depending upon how you use it, it may or may not match your copper.  For example, after filing and/or sanding a soldered joint this solder will look grey.  But do not despair!  Simply heat it back up with your torch until you see a color change and carry on.  The heat from the flame will bring the copper back up to the surface to give you the copper color.  If you are just starting out, practice is the key!
(The second picture shows a sample pure copper chain I made using this brazing wire and 18 gauge #110 bare copper wire. I have even used this solder and the 24ga copper strip I offer to make some really funky belt buckles for my son's steampunk costume! I will try to show you guys a picture soon).
Cut with medium to heavy wire cutters or preferably with solder cutting pliers (your best flush cutting pliers are not recommended).  Soldering your own metal pieces is fun!  Cut into tiny pieces using your wire cutters inside a plastic bag to keep the pieces from flying around the room.  Use safety glasses to protect your eyes from flying pieces of solder!   Do not cut solder in the presence of children or others without eye protection.  Avoid creating and breathing metal dust and fumes in an non-ventilated space.  Always have a carbon monoxide detector in the room with you!  Have fun and be safe creating what you imagine.  
Check out more copper wire and supplies here:
https://www.etsy.com/shop/TheSparkleStore?section_id=15241312&ref=shopsection_leftnav_3
Check back often as I add more varieties of brazing wire with complete disclosure of their metal contents.  
Please use caution when opening the roll to prevent the ends of the coil from springing into face and eyes.

Product name: Tunnel earrings Plug weights Plugs hoops Hoop plugs Tribal earrings Purple gauges Ear plugs Large hoop earrings Large plugs Dangle plugs
Description:
Im stretching my ears since two years and I made those hoops simply because I cannot find anything better to fit with my clothing line. I have collected material over the years and I like to do a lot of various crafts, so those represent my love of handmade, my love of exentricity. By wearing those gypsy loops, you will claim your right to be yourself 😀 
Technical part 😀
Firstly you must have stretched ears to wear those dangles, and they are not intended to be worn on bare lobes. Your tunnels plugs must have a hole large enought to pass the closure trought.
I made those hoop earrings from recycling bangles I own. I use some yarn remnant from my knitting skein, so no waste. The large bead took me ages to do because I wanted large beads without all the weight. I wrapped paper mache, then added clay to smooth the surface and finally ended with my handmade flower clay canes and some paint. 
Weight: around 29 gramms each
Circumference: 4"!
February UPDATE: please take in account that I do my very best to represent the true colors of my items by taking my photos outside in natural light,I use a fuji XT10 camera and no filter at all on etsy. My instagram photography work is not used on Etsy. Each monitors display photos differently. Thank you
This pair is one of a kind and will not be duplicated🍀
If you need any other specific question Im always there to help.
Please take note that this listing only include the earrings hoops, not the tunnel plugs.
I ship my packages with tracking and most of them are received within a week in USA. Multiple orders are usually sent in express (4 days).
You can find me on instagram as @mynoushart https://instagram.com/p/BIzx1w5j23Q/
